==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tomopteris
<hw>To*mop"te*ris</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr.
Gr. <grk>to`mos</grk> a cut + <grk>ptero`n</grk> wing (but taken to
mean, fin).]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A genus of transparent marine
annelids which swim actively at the surface of the sea. They have deeply
divided or forked finlike organs (parapodia). This genus is the type of
the order, or suborder, Gymnocopa.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tomorn</ent>⟦br⟧
